41
00:05:26.590 --> 00:05:31.210
Yikes! I was scared stiff!
Were you scared too, mister?!

42
00:05:26.590 --> 00:05:33.270
Ruins of Kibi, Wano

43
00:05:31.210 --> 00:05:33.270
Could you shut up?

44
00:05:33.270 --> 00:05:36.480
Wowee! That's mighty considerate of you!

45
00:05:36.480 --> 00:05:40.570
You're so subtle in how you care for
my voice. How thoughtful. Thanks!

46
00:05:40.570 --> 00:05:44.690
Oh, sorry for not introducing
myself sooner. My name is Tonoyasu.

47
00:05:40.610 --> 00:05:49.450
Otoko the Kamuro

48
00:05:44.690 --> 00:05:47.830
Everyone calls me Yasu "the Sycophant."

49
00:05:47.830 --> 00:05:49.450
Nice to meet you!

50
00:05:50.500 --> 00:05:54.370
Oh my, you're captivating even
when you don't speak!

51
00:05:54.370 --> 00:05:58.250
You stud, you! The ladies
must be all over you, mister!

52
00:05:59.350 --> 00:06:01.430
Why are you following me?

53
00:06:01.430 --> 00:06:05.170
A thought struck me back
at the gambling house:

54
00:06:05.170 --> 00:06:08.890
"If I follow this man,
everything will be alright."

55
00:06:08.890 --> 00:06:12.790
An ordinary person wouldn't
have messed with those guys.

56
00:06:12.790 --> 00:06:18.440
They're yakuza thugs from the capital's
terrifying Kyoshiro Family.

57
00:06:18.440 --> 00:06:21.440
Oh, what you did was staggering!

58
00:06:21.440 --> 00:06:24.780
If I were a woman, I'd be weak at the knees!

59
00:06:26.700 --> 00:06:28.450
What's the matter, mister?!

60
00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:31.180
That looks familiar.

61
00:06:31.180 --> 00:06:36.200
You're so perceptive! What you see
in the distance is the Flower Capital!

62
00:06:36.200 --> 00:06:39.290
And before that, you'll find
Ebisu, the Leftovers Town!

63
00:06:39.290 --> 00:06:41.290
That's my hometown!

64
00:06:41.290 --> 00:06:44.500
Ebisu...? Like the god of fortune, huh?

65
00:06:44.980 --> 00:06:49.430
Why is it named Ebisu, you wonder?
You'll see once you get there!

66
00:06:55.430 --> 00:06:57.290
I'll take one, too!

67
00:06:57.290 --> 00:06:58.230
Coming right up!

68
00:06:59.200 --> 00:07:01.490
He doesn't look familiar...

69
00:07:01.490 --> 00:07:04.110
Hmm... It sure is popular though...

70
00:07:04.600 --> 00:07:06.780
That squirt...

71
00:07:07.560 --> 00:07:10.650
Doesn't he know who's turf this is?

72
00:07:11.800 --> 00:07:14.810
We oughta show him...

73
00:07:21.420 --> 00:07:23.920
Strike the iron!

74
00:07:29.840 --> 00:07:32.930
Haul the stone!

75
00:07:42.580 --> 00:07:44.770
If you can't work...

76
00:07:44.770 --> 00:07:47.520
you should just die...

77
00:07:47.530 --> 00:07:50.030
and get out of the way!

78
00:07:54.070 --> 00:07:54.120
isoner Mining Ca
Weapons Facto
don, Wan

79
00:07:54.120 --> 00:07:54.160
risoner Mining Cam
Weapons Factor
don, Wan

80
00:07:54.160 --> 00:07:54.200
risoner Mining Cam
Weapons Factor
don, Wan

81
00:07:54.200 --> 00:07:54.240
Prisoner Mining Camp
& Weapons Factory
Udon, Wano

82
00:07:54.240 --> 00:07:54.280
Prisoner Mining Camp
& Weapons Factory
Udon, Wano

83
00:07:54.280 --> 00:07:56.990
Prisoner Mining Camp
& Weapons Factory
Udon, Wano

84
00:08:11.440 --> 00:08:13.800
I-Is this it?

85
00:08:13.800 --> 00:08:18.140
By hauling five big blocks of rock,
you get one millet dumpling!

86
00:08:18.700 --> 00:08:23.900
Are you too decrepit to earn
your own food, old man Hyo?!

87
00:08:24.440 --> 00:08:27.750
Death is finally closing in on you!

88
00:08:30.490 --> 00:08:33.530
I worked all day...

89
00:08:33.530 --> 00:08:36.700
Huh?! What'd you just say?!

90
00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:42.700
The punishment for talking back to a guard...

91
00:08:43.210 --> 00:08:45.170
is dismemberment!

92
00:08:45.770 --> 00:08:47.120
Next!

93
00:08:48.190 --> 00:08:52.340
Old man Hyo! Don't fight. Save your energy!

94
00:08:52.340 --> 00:08:53.900
Or you're gonna die!

95
00:08:55.470 --> 00:08:58.140
Oh, four exchange tickets!

96
00:08:58.140 --> 00:09:00.200
Well done!

97
00:09:08.520 --> 00:09:11.110
Move! Move! Move! Move! Move!

98
00:09:11.110 --> 00:09:13.320
Outta my way!

99
00:09:18.100 --> 00:09:21.240
You guys are in my way!
Do you wanna get run over?!

100
00:09:21.240 --> 00:09:23.870
Watch it, Jaggy!

101
00:09:24.620 --> 00:09:26.620
I'll run you over, too!

102
00:09:52.800 --> 00:09:56.610
Wait, wait! It's already full! That's it for today!

103
00:09:59.030 --> 00:10:01.410
Then, get another ship out here!

104
00:10:01.410 --> 00:10:02.700
You slowpokes!

105
00:10:03.800 --> 00:10:05.250
I-I'm sorry!

106
00:10:10.540 --> 00:10:13.000
How many stones did they haul?

107
00:10:13.000 --> 00:10:15.090
I stopped counting at 500...

108
00:10:15.090 --> 00:10:17.430
Huh?! What about the seastone?!

109
00:10:17.430 --> 00:10:18.260
It's on them!

110
00:10:20.690 --> 00:10:24.100
They pulled that off even while weakened?!

111
00:10:24.700 --> 00:10:29.020
What can they do when the cuffs come off?

112
00:10:29.020 --> 00:10:32.190
I finished my work! Give me food!

113
00:10:34.270 --> 00:10:35.150
What?!

114
00:10:35.800 --> 00:10:37.760
Whaaat?!

115
00:10:54.590 --> 00:10:57.800
How much did they haul
to get that much food?!

116
00:11:02.550 --> 00:11:04.140
What's your problem?!

117
00:11:04.140 --> 00:11:05.430
What're you looking at?!

118
00:11:06.290 --> 00:11:08.350
I got one more than you!

119
00:11:08.350 --> 00:11:10.390
You punk! I outpaced you!

120
00:11:10.390 --> 00:11:13.650
Screw you! No way you beat me, Jaggy!

121
00:11:13.650 --> 00:11:16.650
Can't you even count, you stupid monkey?!

122
00:11:16.650 --> 00:11:18.150
You bastard!

123
00:11:18.150 --> 00:11:20.150
Damn you!

124
00:11:22.900 --> 00:11:26.200
I thought they were both badly injured...

125
00:11:28.990 --> 00:11:34.460
They work, eat, and sleep... They're fully
recovered after just a few days...

126
00:11:34.460 --> 00:11:36.670
How do their bodies work?!

127
00:11:37.450 --> 00:11:40.670
How are we supposed to break their spirits?!

128
00:11:41.740 --> 00:11:43.010
Say something to them!

129
00:11:43.010 --> 00:11:44.260
What?!

130
00:11:49.430 --> 00:11:51.690
Ch-Chew your food!

131
00:11:51.690 --> 00:11:53.310
Are you their mother?!

132
00:12:07.580 --> 00:12:10.160
My dumplings...

133
00:12:19.250 --> 00:12:21.920
Dammit!

134
00:12:23.800 --> 00:12:31.890
Dobon
Vice Warden & Headliner
Hippo SMILE Fruit

135
00:12:25.200 --> 00:12:31.890
Which prisoner ate all
the food we had in storage?!

136
00:12:33.100 --> 00:12:34.390
It's Vice Warden Dobon!

137
00:12:36.520 --> 00:12:38.350
Hippo!

138
00:12:39.190 --> 00:12:42.820
Bring out the perpetrator!

139
00:12:45.820 --> 00:12:47.740
Help...!

140
00:12:47.740 --> 00:12:50.200
Oh! Old man Hyo is trapped!

141
00:12:50.200 --> 00:12:51.950
Crawl out of there, old man!

142
00:12:52.690 --> 00:12:54.210
Vice Warden!

143
00:12:54.210 --> 00:12:55.920
They're behind bars now!

144
00:12:55.920 --> 00:12:58.710
What?! What about the dumplings?!

145
00:12:58.710 --> 00:13:01.090
They ate them all...

146
00:13:01.090 --> 00:13:04.190
You guys just stood there and watched?!

147
00:13:04.190 --> 00:13:06.470
They worked hard to earn that food,

148
00:13:06.470 --> 00:13:10.480
so there wasn't a whole lot we could say...

149
00:13:11.400 --> 00:13:15.490
How dare you disregard
the words of the vice warden!

150
00:13:20.610 --> 00:13:24.030
I can't really hear him since
the hippo closed its mouth...

151
00:13:24.030 --> 00:13:25.200
Hippo?

152
00:13:25.780 --> 00:13:27.200
Vice Warden Dobon...

153
00:13:29.310 --> 00:13:32.410
Bring the culprits here!

154
00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:43.300
Vice Warden, here they are!

155
00:13:45.420 --> 00:13:47.300
These two are responsible!

156
00:13:56.860 --> 00:13:58.770
– They're stuffed!
– They're stuffed!

157
00:13:58.770 --> 00:14:02.320
I've never seen anyone around
here with a full belly before!

158
00:14:02.320 --> 00:14:04.190
They're so lucky!

159
00:14:04.190 --> 00:14:05.990
Damn you...!

160
00:14:05.990 --> 00:14:09.570
I'm a big eater, but thanks to you pigs,

161
00:14:09.570 --> 00:14:11.450
I only got three dumplings!

162
00:14:11.450 --> 00:14:14.580
Look at this mouth! Think that was enough?!

163
00:14:14.580 --> 00:14:16.750
Of course it wasn't!

164
00:14:17.700 --> 00:14:19.820
Wait a minute...

165
00:14:19.820 --> 00:14:22.090
I need to digest this...

166
00:14:35.600 --> 00:14:37.060
– What?!
– What?!

167
00:14:43.940 --> 00:14:47.360
I don't wanna see prisoners
looking so satisfied!

168
00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:52.350
That was my food!

169
00:14:56.880 --> 00:15:00.250
Hey! Don't push your luck, you worms!

170
00:15:00.250 --> 00:15:06.000
Listen up! If you mess with the guards...

171
00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:08.550
the first offense will cost you your arms!

172
00:15:09.840 --> 00:15:12.260
For the second, your legs!

173
00:15:14.150 --> 00:15:15.890
And if there is a third,

174
00:15:15.890 --> 00:15:18.100
you'll be sentenced to death!

175
00:15:18.100 --> 00:15:19.930
You've been warned!

176
00:15:21.230 --> 00:15:26.980
He's right! You guys have
no right to fight back!

177
00:15:26.980 --> 00:15:32.700
Hey, we're weaklings at the moment,
thanks to the seastone.

178
00:15:33.300 --> 00:15:35.700
All we did was work hard.

179
00:15:37.100 --> 00:15:40.160
Your crime was...

180
00:15:45.610 --> 00:15:49.590
eating all my food!

181
00:15:52.840 --> 00:15:54.260
Son of a...!

182
00:15:54.260 --> 00:15:55.350
Jaggy!

183
00:16:01.560 --> 00:16:03.810
Hippo!

184
00:16:04.440 --> 00:16:09.150
I'll teach you discipline!

185
00:16:10.400 --> 00:16:12.400
Whoa! He ate them!

186
00:16:12.400 --> 00:16:14.610
Poor saps!

187
00:16:14.610 --> 00:16:18.910
The inside of Vice Warden Dobon's
mouth is a slaughterhouse!

188
00:16:40.700 --> 00:16:42.640
What happened?!

189
00:16:42.640 --> 00:16:46.440
I've never seen the hippo go down like this!

190
00:16:54.180 --> 00:16:56.840
Vice Warden Dobon?!

191
00:17:11.300 --> 00:17:15.930
Look what you did! Just try
and escape the death penalty now!

192
00:17:19.200 --> 00:17:20.760
Prove it.

193
00:17:20.760 --> 00:17:21.640
What?!

194
00:17:23.090 --> 00:17:26.560
I'm saying you need to prove it!

195
00:17:33.030 --> 00:17:35.700
Way to go, you guys!

196
00:17:35.700 --> 00:17:38.570
This makes you heroes to the rest of us!

197
00:17:57.410 --> 00:18:02.600
Get some special soba!
Sangoro's special soba!

198
00:18:12.480 --> 00:18:16.570
It's Sangoro's special soba!

199
00:18:19.160 --> 00:18:21.120
I'd like to try some right away!

200
00:18:25.410 --> 00:18:28.730
Here! Thank you for waiting!

201
00:18:25.410 --> 00:18:31.250
Special  Soba

202
00:18:28.730 --> 00:18:31.250
Oh, it looks tasty!

203
00:18:45.790 --> 00:18:50.190
So good! This is insanely delicious!

204
00:18:50.190 --> 00:18:52.270
Any word on Luffy?

205
00:18:52.270 --> 00:18:55.940
He's at the prisoner
mining camp in Udon, right?

206
00:18:55.940 --> 00:19:01.890
It's pretty far from here, but I'm sure
he'll bust out before the big day.

207
00:19:02.870 --> 00:19:08.620
It's nice to eat your food again, Sanji!
I'm glad that you came back safely!

208
00:19:11.880 --> 00:19:14.710
I don't care if you like it...

209
00:19:15.320 --> 00:19:18.970
Orobi my lovely! How does it taste?

210
00:19:19.500 --> 00:19:21.800
Well, it tastes incredible!

211
00:19:21.800 --> 00:19:25.350
Orobi as a geisha is more incredible!

212
00:19:26.890 --> 00:19:28.140
Anyway...

213
00:19:28.610 --> 00:19:31.980
the soba is good, but it's only drawing girls.

214
00:19:31.980 --> 00:19:36.110
Attract samurai by whipping up
something spicy that pairs with sake!

215
00:19:40.800 --> 00:19:45.570
What's with that look?! Don't you wanna
recruit more allies, you bum?!

216
00:19:49.310 --> 00:19:52.730
Wait, Franky! Here come some male customers now.

217
00:19:53.670 --> 00:19:55.330
Pardon us.

218
00:19:55.330 --> 00:19:57.710
Excuse us, ladies!

219
00:19:57.710 --> 00:20:00.800
Hey guys, don't cut!

220
00:20:01.900 --> 00:20:06.010
Huh?! You got something to say?!
Shut your mouth!

221
00:20:08.180 --> 00:20:09.850
It's the Kyoshiro Family...

222
00:20:09.850 --> 00:20:10.930
What?!

223
00:20:13.100 --> 00:20:14.770
Hey, outta our way!

224
00:20:18.150 --> 00:20:21.780
This place seems to be thriving, young man!

225
00:20:21.780 --> 00:20:24.320
Yeah, I'm thrilled!

226
00:20:24.320 --> 00:20:29.080
Special  Soba
Are you guys customers?
If you wanna eat, get in line!

227
00:20:29.080 --> 00:20:32.170
No, we just wondering something...

228
00:20:32.170 --> 00:20:36.460
Who gave you permission to do business here?

229
00:20:39.670 --> 00:20:43.190
We're from the Kyoshiro Family,
and this is our turf...

230
00:20:43.190 --> 00:20:47.800
Unless you pay us, you're not
allowed to run a shop here!

231
00:20:44.550 --> 00:20:47.800
Kaku, Kuni, Suke
Kyoshiro Family

232
00:20:47.800 --> 00:20:50.680
Oh, is that so?

233
00:20:51.930 --> 00:20:55.350
Those people... I think they're...

234
00:20:56.670 --> 00:20:58.480
You know something about them?

235
00:20:58.480 --> 00:21:03.820
Yes, the other day, I was at
the banquet hall of a man named Kyoshiro.

236
00:21:04.450 --> 00:21:08.280
Shogun Orochi is a coward!

237
00:21:12.830 --> 00:21:16.120
Sake! Bring me more sake!

238
00:21:19.460 --> 00:21:24.840
He was an extremely arrogant samurai.
It seems like he's a yakuza boss.

239
00:21:24.840 --> 00:21:28.510
These men are likely his underlings.

240
00:21:29.470 --> 00:21:33.720
Hey, are you deaf?! I said you gotta pay up!

241
00:21:33.720 --> 00:21:34.680
Why?

242
00:21:35.800 --> 00:21:40.440
Why? Because if you don't, we can't protect
you if someone attacks your stand.

243
00:21:41.290 --> 00:21:45.280
I don't need your help. I'm pretty tough.

244
00:21:47.200 --> 00:21:49.200
Here, thank you for waiting!

245
00:21:49.200 --> 00:21:50.740
Thanks!

246
00:22:03.590 --> 00:22:05.880
You think you're tough?

247
00:22:05.880 --> 00:22:09.340
Then, just try to protect your shop!

248
00:22:10.680 --> 00:22:12.140
Soba!

249
00:22:12.140 --> 00:22:13.680
Hey!

250
00:22:13.680 --> 00:22:16.100
Don't eat the soba from this place!

251
00:22:27.680 --> 00:22:31.410
Is she crying or laughing?

252
00:22:31.410 --> 00:22:33.910
My soba!

253
00:22:38.370 --> 00:22:41.920
Oh no! This will piss off Sanji
more than anything!

254
00:22:41.920 --> 00:22:45.510
Beat it, ladies! The shop's closed for the day!

255
00:22:47.670 --> 00:22:50.640
Go, get outta here! He ran out of soba!

256
00:22:52.680 --> 00:22:55.810
Come on! Just get lost!

257
00:23:01.180 --> 00:23:03.060
Oh no! We'd better get outta the way!

258
00:23:04.400 --> 00:23:05.570
Hey!

259
00:23:07.910 --> 00:23:09.450
What do you want?

260
00:23:10.760 --> 00:23:13.450
I'm gonna need you to finish your food...

261
00:23:14.130 --> 00:23:15.580
dear customer.

262
00:23:15.580 --> 00:23:18.750
Huh?! You wanna fight, punk?!

263
00:23:18.750 --> 00:23:21.040
Hey! Suke! Kaku!

264
00:23:21.040 --> 00:23:22.500
Yeah!

265
00:23:22.500 --> 00:23:24.430
Let's rough him up!

266
00:23:25.540 --> 00:23:28.920
Hmm?! A fight?!

267
00:23:28.920 --> 00:23:30.800
Go to hell!

268
00:23:36.590 --> 00:23:38.470
You bastard!

269
00:23:48.370 --> 00:23:50.720
Ow, ow, ow...

270
00:23:58.900 --> 00:24:00.120
Damn it!

271
00:24:03.210 --> 00:24:04.880
Die!

272
00:24:23.690 --> 00:24:25.210
Ow, ow, ow...

273
00:24:27.800 --> 00:24:29.820
Big Bro!

274
00:24:31.690 --> 00:24:34.660
What with this soba cook?! He's so strong!

275
00:24:34.660 --> 00:24:37.160
That soba guy is so cool!

276
00:24:37.160 --> 00:24:40.870
Sanji, save some for me!

277
00:24:45.170 --> 00:24:47.080
Here we go!

278
00:24:47.080 --> 00:24:50.800
Stop! Dammit! What are you doing to me?!

279
00:24:50.800 --> 00:24:54.500
Franosuke Iron...

280
00:24:59.640 --> 00:25:02.830
Suplex!

281
00:25:11.150 --> 00:25:12.950
That carpenter, too?!

282
00:25:12.950 --> 00:25:14.820
They shouldn't have done that!

283
00:25:26.400 --> 00:25:29.710
Now, eat every last bite!

284
00:25:29.710 --> 00:25:33.460
You're gonna eat every bit
of soba you wasted!

285
00:25:34.170 --> 00:25:37.260
Here, eat up! Don't let any go to waste!

286
00:25:35.140 --> 00:25:37.260
Big Bro! Big Bro!

287
00:25:37.260 --> 00:25:39.690
What? You want some?!

288
00:25:40.350 --> 00:25:43.120
You'll regret this!

289
00:25:45.200 --> 00:25:47.850
Now, wakey wakey!

290
00:25:50.520 --> 00:25:53.150
Nice doing business!

291
00:25:53.150 --> 00:25:58.330
Well, that's about what I expected,
but was it a good idea to kick their asses?

292
00:25:59.990 --> 00:26:03.250
Perhaps messing with them
wasn't the best idea...

293
00:26:03.790 --> 00:26:07.650
That long line of customers
scattered like roaches.

294
00:26:07.650 --> 00:26:11.170
This is usually when
the big bruiser comes along.

295
00:26:16.420 --> 00:26:18.970
She's the girl who had her soba knocked over.

296
00:26:18.970 --> 00:26:22.220
She's an oddball, crying and
laughing at the same time.

297
00:26:22.220 --> 00:26:23.760
Huh? Wait a sec...

298
00:26:23.760 --> 00:26:25.020
What is it?

299
00:26:25.020 --> 00:26:28.480
I've seen her somewhere before...

300
00:26:34.700 --> 00:26:36.570
All right!

301
00:26:36.570 --> 00:26:39.240
I made a killing!

302
00:26:39.240 --> 00:26:41.820
I didn't think I'd sell this much!

303
00:26:46.580 --> 00:26:47.950
What do you want?

304
00:26:48.500 --> 00:26:52.290
Hey, so that's a medicine that
heals any kind of wound?

305
00:26:52.290 --> 00:26:54.340
Huh? Why, yes!

306
00:26:54.340 --> 00:26:57.010
This will stop bleeding and ease pain!

307
00:26:57.010 --> 00:27:00.880
This toad oil is a surefire remedy!

308
00:27:01.840 --> 00:27:04.450
That's amazing!

309
00:27:05.020 --> 00:27:07.470
I met her at the shrine.

310
00:27:15.570 --> 00:27:20.030
Sorry about the trouble earlier.

311
00:27:20.030 --> 00:27:24.030
There was still soba left over.
Please have some!

312
00:27:24.030 --> 00:27:27.410
Whoa! Thank you!

313
00:27:41.510 --> 00:27:42.930
It's...

314
